  { slug: 'selling-in-richlands',            name: 'Richlands',            summary: "Richlands has something its immediate neighbours do not: a Springfield Central line train station. That rail access, combined with genuine family character and upgrader-friendly price points, shapes who buys here and what they will pay." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-riverhills',           name: 'Riverhills',           summary: "Riverhills' larger blocks, elevated positions and Centenary Motorway access make it a consistent choice for families wanting space, outlook and convenience. Selling here means understanding an experienced western Brisbane buyer pool that knows what it wants." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-robertson',            name: 'Robertson',            summary: "Robertson's quiet southern Brisbane position, family-upgrader buyer profile, and school catchment appeal create consistent demand that rewards sellers who understand the comparison market in Macgregor and Sunnybank Hills." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-rochedale',            name: 'Rochedale',            summary: "Rochedale's modern family estates, the Rochedale State School catchment, and the older acreage pockets in the east attract committed family buyers from across south Brisbane and interstate. Here is what sellers need to know in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-rocklea',              name: 'Rocklea',              summary: "Rocklea's affordable southern Brisbane position, industrial-residential boundary dynamics, and strong investor yield demand create a niche market where understanding the buyer profile is essential for sellers in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-runcorn',              name: 'Runcorn',              summary: "Runcorn's family-friendly southern Brisbane position, strong school catchments, and affordable entry relative to Sunnybank attract upgrader buyers who move quickly when a well-prepared home is priced correctly." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-salisbury',            name: 'Salisbury',            summary: "Salisbury's Pacific Motorway access, post-war family character, and affordable entry relative to nearby Moorooka attract buyers looking for southern Brisbane value. Here is what sellers need to know in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-seven-hills',          name: 'Seven Hills',          summary: "Seven Hills' elevated position, large allotments, and proximity to Morningside and Camp Hill make it one of the inner east's most competitive renovation and rebuild markets." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-seventeen-mile-rocks', name: 'Seventeen Mile Rocks', summary: "Seventeen Mile Rocks' quiet western Brisbane riverside character, established family demographic and Centenary Motorway access create a market that rewards sellers who run the right campaign for the right buyer in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-sherwood',             name: 'Sherwood',             summary: "Sherwood's inner south-west position, character homes, and proximity to Graceville and Chelmer buyers create a market where the right campaign and pricing strategy consistently outperforms." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-sinnamon-park',        name: 'Sinnamon Park',        summary: "Sinnamon Park's estate lifestyle, park-fronting block premiums, and western Brisbane family buyer profile make it a niche market where position relative to parks and outlook drives significant price differences." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-south-brisbane',       name: 'South Brisbane',       summary: "South Brisbane's high-density inner-city apartment market rewards sellers who understand strata records, rental yields, and how to position against competing stock in the South Bank precinct." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-spring-hill',          name: 'Spring Hill',          summary: "Spring Hill's CBD walkability and character cottage market are increasingly sought after by professional buyers. Here is what sellers need to know about this inner-city market in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-springwood',           name: 'Springwood',           summary: "Springwood's hub status, major retail precinct, Pacific Motorway access, and diverse housing stock attract a broad buyer pool of families, first home buyers and investors. Here is what sellers need to know about positioning and timing in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-st-lucia',             name: 'St Lucia',             summary: "St Lucia's UQ effect, large character blocks, and inner west position attract an educated, patient buyer pool that responds to accurate pricing and well-timed campaigns." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-stafford',             name: 'Stafford',             summary: "Stafford's inner north family market, school catchments, and value position relative to Kedron and Nundah create reliable buyer demand for sellers who price accurately in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-stafford-heights',     name: 'Stafford Heights',     summary: "Stafford Heights is an established north Brisbane family suburb with Kedron Brook access and strong Westfield Chermside proximity. Here is what sellers need to know before listing in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-stones-corner',        name: 'Stones Corner',        summary: "Stones Corner's village centre, heritage buildings, and improving amenity attract a growing buyer pool that values character and walkability over land size." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-sumner',               name: 'Sumner',               summary: "Sumner's quiet established western Brisbane character, Centenary Motorway access, generous blocks, and low stock turnover create a market dominated by long-term holders and upsizing families. Here is what sellers need to know in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-sunnybank',            name: 'Sunnybank',            summary: "Sunnybank's multicultural southern Brisbane character, diverse buyer pool, and strong investor demand create a market with unique buyer dynamics that rewards sellers who understand the local purchaser profile." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-sunnybank-hills',      name: 'Sunnybank Hills',      summary: "Sunnybank Hills' multicultural character, broad buyer pool, and investor demand sit alongside strong owner-occupier demand. Here is what sellers need to know about positioning in this distinctive southern Brisbane market." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-taigum',               name: 'Taigum',               summary: "Taigum is a compact northern suburb with practical amenity, consistent buyer demand and an entry point that sits below most of its northern corridor neighbours. Here is what sellers need to know before listing in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-tarragindi',           name: 'Tarragindi',           summary: "Tarragindi's quiet family streetscape, post-war block sizes, and affordable entry relative to Annerley and Greenslopes give sellers a strong story to tell buyer-upgraders." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-teneriffe',            name: 'Teneriffe',            summary: "Teneriffe's woolstore conversions, riverfront apartments, and proximity to New Farm position it as one of Brisbane's premium inner-city markets for apartment vendors." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-tennyson',             name: 'Tennyson',             summary: "Tennyson's tight river bend, the Queensland Tennis Centre precinct and the Tennyson Reach apartments create one of Brisbane's smallest and most tightly held prestige markets. Here is what sellers need to know in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-tingalpa',             name: 'Tingalpa',             summary: "Tingalpa's large blocks, gateway access, and value position relative to Murarrie and Cannon Hill attract a specific family buyer who prioritises space over inner-city proximity." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-toowong',              name: 'Toowong',              summary: "Toowong's river access, transit connections and proximity to UQ and Wesley Hospital underpin one of Brisbane's most consistent inner-west family markets. Here is what sellers need to know in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-underwood',            name: 'Underwood',            summary: "Underwood's Marketplace precinct, Mansfield State High catchment and Pacific Motorway access create a distinct southern Brisbane buyer pool. Here is what sellers need to know about timing and positioning in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-upper-kedron',         name: 'Upper Kedron',         summary: "Upper Kedron's semi-rural outer northern character, generous blocks and quieter family streets create a market where well-presented homes consistently outperform broader corridor benchmarks for sellers in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-upper-mount-gravatt',  name: 'Upper Mount Gravatt',  summary: "Upper Mount Gravatt's greenspace access, large family blocks, and Westfield proximity make it a reliable performer at the upper end of the southside family market." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-virginia',             name: 'Virginia',             summary: "Virginia's northern Brisbane investment appeal, airport corridor location, and affordable entry attract both investors and owner-occupiers. Here is what sellers need to know about positioning and timing in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-wakerley',             name: 'Wakerley',             summary: "Wakerley's modern executive estates, larger family blocks and bayside-reach lifestyle attract a deliberate family buyer from across the inner east and the eastern corridor. Here is what sellers need to know in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-wavell-heights',       name: 'Wavell Heights',       summary: "Wavell Heights' elevated inner north-east position, strong school catchments, and consistent capital growth from low turnover make it one of Brisbane's most stable family markets for sellers." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-west-end',             name: 'West End',             summary: "West End's inner-south multicultural character, character worker's cottages, and Boundary Street strip attract a diverse buyer pool that includes both investors and owner-occupiers." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-wilston',              name: 'Wilston',              summary: "Wilston's heritage Queenslanders, low stock turnover, and loyal owner-occupier base make it one of Brisbane's inner north's most consistent premium performers. Here is what sellers need to know in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-windsor',              name: 'Windsor',              summary: "Windsor's inner north character homes, strong buyer spillover from Fortitude Valley and Newstead, and improving village amenity create a fast-moving market for sellers who understand the profile." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-wishart',              name: 'Wishart',              summary: "Wishart's established southern Brisbane family character, larger blocks than nearby suburbs, and strong school catchments create consistent demand from upgrading families looking for more space within the inner south-east." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-woolloongabba',        name: 'Woolloongabba',        summary: "Woolloongabba's ongoing regeneration, Gabba precinct, and improving amenity are reshaping its buyer profile. Here is what sellers need to know about this transitioning market in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-wooloowin',            name: 'Wooloowin',            summary: "Wooloowin's Doomben line advantage, inner north character homes, and buyer demand from Nundah and Kedron make it an underrated suburb where sellers consistently achieve strong results." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-wynnum',               name: 'Wynnum',               summary: "Wynnum's premium Esplanade position, bayside lifestyle, and mix of family and downsizer buyers create a market where understanding buyer motivation drives better results than simply tracking median prices." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-wynnum-west',          name: 'Wynnum West',          summary: "Wynnum West's bayside lifestyle access, young family buyer profile, and value position relative to Wynnum make it one of eastern Brisbane's most consistent affordable family markets for sellers in 2026." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-yeronga',              name: 'Yeronga',              summary: "Yeronga's repricing inner south market, improving amenity, and river proximity attract a buyer profile that has been watching the suburb for years. Sellers in 2026 are well-positioned to capture that demand." },
  { slug: 'selling-in-zillmere',             name: 'Zillmere',             summary: "Zillmere's train station proximity, large post-war blocks, and active first-home buyer and investor pool create a comparison-active market where accurate pricing is the single biggest driver of campaign outcomes for sellers." },
];
---
<Layout title="Selling Property in Brisbane Suburbs | Daniel Gierach Property" description="Suburb-by-suburb guides to selling property in Brisbane. Covering 162 suburbs with local market conditions, what drives value, and selling strategy." schema={clusterSchema}>

<article style="background:var(--color-surface-0);min-height:100vh;">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div style="background:#e6d9bd;padding:8rem 0 3.5rem;">
    <div class="max-w-[1100px] mx-auto px-8">
      <a href="/insights" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:0.65rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(25,24,23,0.6);text-decoration:none;margin-bottom:2rem;transition:color 0.2s;"
        onmouseover="this.style.color='#6b4610'" onmouseout="this.style.color='rgba(25,24,23,0.6)'" onclick="if(history.length>1&&document.referrer.indexOf(location.origin)===0){history.back();return false}">
        &larr; Back
      </a>
      <span style="display:block;font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:0.6rem;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#6b4610;margin-bottom:1rem;">Suburb Directory &middot; 162 Guides</span>
      <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:clamp(2rem,5vw,3.25rem);font-weight:400;color:#191817;line-height:1.12;letter-spacing:-0.02em;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        Selling Property in Brisbane Suburbs
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(25,24,23,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:58ch;">
        Every Brisbane suburb sells differently. School catchments, days-on-market data, what drives buyer competition, and what the current market looks like in your street all vary at the suburb level. Find your suburb below for a specific, data-led guide.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Suburb Directory -->
  <div style="padding:3.5rem 0 5rem;background:var(--color-base);">
    <div class="max-w-[1100px] mx-auto px-8">

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(320px,1fr));gap:1rem;">
        {suburbs.map(s => (
          <a href={`/insights/${s.slug}`}
            style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid rgba(28,25,23,0.1);padding:1.5rem;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.6rem;text-decoration:none;transition:background 0.2s,border-color 0.2s,transform 0.25s,box-shadow 0.25s;position:relative;overflow:hidden;box-shadow:0 1px 4px rgba(28,25,23,0.05);"
            onmouseover="this.style.background='#f2ead4';this.style.borderColor='rgba(185,130,41,0.3)';this.style.transform='translateY(-3px)';this.style.boxShadow='0 8px 24px rgba(28,25,23,0.09)'"
            onmouseout="this.style.background='#ffffff';this.style.borderColor='rgba(28,25,23,0.1)';this.style.transform='translateY(0)';this.style.boxShadow='0 1px 4px rgba(28,25,23,0.05)'"
          >
            <div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:2px;background:#6b4610;"></div>
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;">
              <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1rem;font-weight:400;color:#191817;line-height:1.2;">{s.name}</h2>
              <svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#b98229" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
            </div>
            <p style="font-size:0.78rem;color:#78716c;line-height:1.7;">{s.summary}</p>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <div style="padding:4rem 0;background:#f7f5f0;border-top:1px solid rgba(28,25,23,0.08);">
    <div class="max-w-[1100px] mx-auto px-8" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;text-align:center;gap:1.25rem;">
      <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.25rem;font-style:italic;color:#191817;">Not sure how your suburb is performing right now?</p>
      <p style="font-size:0.85rem;color:#78716c;line-height:1.75;max-width:44ch;">Daniel can give you a current read on days-on-market, clearance rates, and what comparable sales suggest about your property's value. No cost, no obligation.</p>
      <a href="/get-an-appraisal" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.6rem;padding:0.85rem 1.75rem;background:#b98229;color:#fff;font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:0.7rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;text-decoration:none;transition:background 0.2s;border-radius:8px;"
        onmouseover="this.style.background='#a87824'" onmouseout="this.style.background='#b98229'">
        Get a Free Appraisal
        <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

</article>

</Layout>
